My 5 year old daughter loves the electronic book and I'm glad she does. It's a fun story by Dr. Seuss with colorful illustrations just like the paperbooks but with the bonus of funny sound effects, great narration, and auto play. I love the convenience of having the book ready for her anytime, anywhere, and, knock on wood, it hasn't failed yet. I also appreciate that the highlighted scrolling allows her to read along with the narrator; I notice her silently sounding out the words to herself. It's worth it.
